<subSubSection pageId="17" pageNumber="58" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="17" pageNumber="58">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="17" pageNumber="58">
<taxonomicName genus="P." lsidName="P. mina" pageId="17" pageNumber="58" rank="species" species="mina">P. mina</taxonomicName>
was recorded for the first time on marginal bedrock of a mountain stream, at 1270 m a.s.l. (
<geoCoordinate direction="south" orientation="latitude" precision="15" value="-20.42">20°25'12&quot;S</geoCoordinate>
, 
<geoCoordinate direction="west" orientation="longitude" precision="1" value="-41.845997">41°50'45.6&quot;W</geoCoordinate>
), in Serra do 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Caparaó">Caparao</normalizedToken>
(
<normalizedToken originalValue="Espírito">Espirito</normalizedToken>
Santo State) (
<bibRefCitation author="Trivinho-Strixino, S" journalOrPublisher="Annales de Limnologie" pageId="30" pageNumber="71" pagination="411 - 423" title="DNA barcoding of Podonomus (Chironomidae, Podonominae) enables stage association of a named species and reveals hidden diversity in Brazilian inselbergs." url="https://doi.org/10.1051/limn/2012032" volume="48" year="2012">Trivinho-Strixino et al. 2012</bibRefCitation>
), but only larvae have been evidenced and the description was only possible after the molecular association with the adults (
<bibRefCitation author="Shimabukuro, EM" journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa" pageId="29" pageNumber="70" pagination="155 - 166" title="Two new species of Podonomus Philippi (Diptera: Chironomidae: Podonominae) from mountains of Southeastern Brazil." url="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.4290.1.9" volume="4290" year="2017 b">Shimabukuro et al. 2017b</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName genus="P." lsidName="P. mina" pageId="17" pageNumber="58" rank="species" species="mina">P. mina</taxonomicName>
was recorded in isolated seepages and rocky substrate in the stream edges from 2575-2700 m a.s.l. in APASM (Minas Gerais State) (
<bibRefCitation author="Shimabukuro, EM" journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa" pageId="29" pageNumber="70" pagination="155 - 166" title="Two new species of Podonomus Philippi (Diptera: Chironomidae: Podonominae) from mountains of Southeastern Brazil." url="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.4290.1.9" volume="4290" year="2017 b">Shimabukuro et al. 2017b</bibRefCitation>
). Water temperature varied from 15-22 °C; dissolved oxygen 6.4-10.2 mg.l-1; pH 5.0-5.5; fast water flow; vegetal coverage completely absent Significant altitudinal specificity have been found (IndVal: 0.41; p = 0.04).
</paragraph>
